    <text id="F3517T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Frank Grube, an assistant surgeon, requests leave prior to a temporary transfer
                    from the 126th Pennsylvania to the 134th Pennsylvania.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head> Med. Dept. 134th Regt. Pa. 
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. Purviance<lb/> Adj. 134th Pa.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-02-14">February 14, 1863</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Having just received the enclosed order from the Surgeon Genls. office--which
                    which with the accompanying endorsements fix the date of my examination there on
                    the twenty third (23rd instant. I respectfully request leave of absence for
                    fifteen days (15) beginning February twenty first (21)--to comply with its terms
                    and make some private arrangements preparatory to my transfer.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully Your Obt. Servt.</salute>
                    <signed>frank grube, asst. Surg., 126 Reg. Pa.<lb/> temporarily detailed to
                        134th Pa.<lb/>
                        <hi rend="underline">and Citizen of the State of Kansas</hi></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
